    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1087"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1087">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Newel</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 80.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that immediately upon
                    receipt of the news of the sad disaster to the cruiser <hi rend="italic"
                        >Maine</hi> the minister of foreign affairs personally called upon me to
                    express the deep sympathy of his Government, and also that the Spanish and
                    German ministers to this court took an early opportunity of evincing their deep
                    regret and condolence with the American people.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stanford Newel.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
